summary: SummaryHighlightsSustainable PackagingBobbi Brown's natural-looking Skin Color Corrector Stick neutralizes dark undereye circles and other discoloration around the face for up to 12 hours of coverage.
details: DetailsBenefitsColor corrects dark undereye circles & other discoloration around the face for instant brighteningDelivers immediate & 12 hour moisture for smoother and plumper skin, perfectly prepped for concealerGlides on buildable coverage that is non-creasing & waterproofLong-wearingAvailable in various color-correcting pink & peach-based shades formulated for all types of discolorationFormulated without parabens, phthalates & sulfates SLS and SLESFeatures12 hour wear, no creasing or cakingColor true for 12 hours - reduces the appearance of dark circles all day12 hour moistureImmediate & 1 week moistureWaterproof, including sweat & humidity resistantKey IngredientsCoffee seed extract & Salicornia: Infuses skin with immediate and long-term moistureItem 2595288How To UseAfter priming face with Vitamin Enriched Face Base Moisturizer & Primer and undereyes with Vitamin Enriched Eye Base Cream & Primer, swipe on corrector over dark circles, dark spots, or discoloration to neutralize, brighten, and even the skin. Pat with finger to blend. Follow with Skin Concealer Stick for a seamless, real-skin coverage.IngredientsLight Bisque: Glyceryl Triacetyl Ricinoleate, Octyldodecanol, Bis-Diglyceryl Polyacyladipate-2, Synthetic Wax, Ozokerite, Kaolin, Barium Sulfate, Calcium Aluminum Borosilicate, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Tocopheryl Acetate, Salicornia Herbacea Extract, Coffea Arabica (Coffee) Seed Oil, Alumina, Silica, Lecithin, Bht, Phenoxyethanol. May Contain (+/-): Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491), Iron Oxides (CI 77492), Iron Oxides (CI 77499), Bismuth Oxychloride (CI 77163) [Iln52330].Ingredients are subject to change at the manufacturer's discretion. For the most complete and up-to-date list of ingredients, refer to the product packaging.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: After priming face with Vitamin Enriched Face Base Moisturizer & Primer and undereyes with Vitamin Enriched Eye Base Cream & Primer, swipe on corrector over dark circles, dark spots, or discoloration to neutralize, brighten, and even the skin. Pat with finger to blend. Follow with Skin Concealer Stick for a seamless, real-skin coverage.

reviews.headline: Smooth but oily
reviews.comments: I like this concealer but it leaves me feeling really oily after use. It's very small. For the price I would not recommend.

reviews.headline: Love This Product
reviews.comments: This has helped diminish the look of dark circles under my eyes. I also use this for darker hyperpigmentation throughout my face. It seems to fade them away. A little pricey for the size but doesn't dry down and makes me look more awake!

reviews.headline: Doesn't cover
reviews.comments: Tried this a couple times and it did not cover my dark spots. Returned it for a refund.

reviews.headline: Love this!
reviews.comments: I have been buying Bobbi Brown's under eye corrector for years.  The under eye corrector comes in a small pot and it camouflages my under eye circles very well.  I love that this corrector is in the form of a stick!  For me, it's simply the best as I've tried less expensive correctors,, but none compare to Bobbi Brown.  I guess you get what you pay for!

reviews.headline: Best Option for dark under eyes
reviews.comments: If your under eye still looks grey or dark even when you use concealer or you simply need to brighten your under eye for a no makeup look this will become your holy grail product. This product is perfection on its own or you can use it before your concealer but you literally will not need a concealer if you use this properly. Pair this with the Bobbi Brown eye base and it will take years off your face.

reviews.headline: Deserted Island Product...
reviews.comments: I always apply after my eyecream is absorbed. Color a bit around the eyes with this stick and dab to blend, they apply concealer. I found the trick is the eye cream to hydrate the area so I can avoid it looking cakey. Then it lasts all day until I take it off at night.

reviews.headline: Skin corrector eyes
reviews.comments: It's extremely small, it seemed better quality and Expensive for its size.

reviews.headline: Excellent product
reviews.comments: This corrector stick is the best that I've used so far. It's creamy and goes on so smoothly and is easy to use under the puffiness that I'm blessed with. I also use it on discolorations on my face with great results.

reviews.headline: Great color corrector
reviews.comments: I am light to medium olive skin with purpleish circles. The color "bisque" almost perfectly conceals them them on its own. I go for a little to no make up look so I apply it by building, focusing on the worst part of the circle, blending down and well. It has not caked up or looks heavy. I'm sure combined with my tinted moisturizer it would be near flawless. TBD

reviews.headline: Waterproof and sweat proof in Texas summer humidity
reviews.comments:
OK, so I've been using this for over a year now.
Not sure why it is taking me this long to review it . I love this stuff. Nothing else has ever covered like this stuff.
I get dark circles from not sleeping enough, from allergies constantly, and genetics! Yay me!
I've tried a lot of other ones, they are OK but they usually crease . This stuff has allowed me to go for no make up days. I just put this on my dark circles and I'm good to go. I can be out in the 100¬∞ Texas heat and it doesn't sweat off or run.
I can put this on in early a.m‚Ä¶ and by 3 PM go get in the pool.. it really is waterproof! It never changes colors or wears off until you wash it off.
When I tan .. the peach color is too light. I do need to go to the bisque.
And the price point is not attractive. But only on my second tube in a year.

reviews.headline: THE best color corrector!!
reviews.comments: I'm 39 and have thin, textured undereyes with dark circles. I have tried a TON of color correctors (Huda, Tarte Creaseless, Catrice, Nars liquid and eye brightener, Bobbi Brown in the pot). Many of them are in less skin-like hues, in textures that either dry down to enhance every line and pore, or cake up once layered over with another product. This comes in the best shade range that, on no makeup days I find I can even use on its own. I generally put a bit of this in my hand then prime it into a fluffy brush before I apply it to my face, which allows me to build it up slowly and keeps it from accentuating any texture.

reviews.headline: Perfect
reviews.comments: Heard the rumors that this would cover circles but didn't believe enough to try it til now. Wow. So glad I did!

reviews.headline: Color corrector
reviews.comments: Overall a great color corrector. It matches my dark under eye shadows perfectly. And it's a cream so doesn't run off.

reviews.headline: Yes! I would buy it again
reviews.comments: Loveee it! I have genetic dark circles and this absolutely covers them.

reviews.headline: Best color corrector
reviews.comments: ABSOLUTELY the BEST color corrector I have ever tried. This color corrector is creamy blend in nicely and can even double up as a concealer! Absolutely amazing would 100% recommend!

reviews.headline: Amazing product
reviews.comments: The skin correct stick has been so good and easy to use. The turn tool is functional & when applied it's easy to blend out covering up the dark circles or unwanted spots. I couldn't recommend this product more. Will always purchase this

reviews.headline: Wonderful!
reviews.comments: Great product!!! After trying so many color correctors, this is the best. The consistency is perfect for coverage of dark/hallow circles. With just a few pats of your finger it melts right in with no greasy or dry look. Worth it!

reviews.headline: Not for mature skin
reviews.comments: Simply doesn't work for skin over 40. Might work better for people in their 20s. Not for me.

reviews.headline: Probably not
reviews.comments: It didn't hide my dark circles no matter how much I applied on or how little.  It didn't matter if i tapped it on or used a brush. The product is thick and it doesn't cover. My understanding eys felt uncomfortable. I'd return it if I could.

reviews.headline: Color blends brilliantly
reviews.comments: This blends out smoothly, color matches seamlessly.. I'm 52, finding under eye color correction, or concealer that actually blurs not creases, is always a challenge. This worked.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I've been using the Bobbi Brown Skin Corrector Stick in Light Bisque for a few weeks, and it's quickly become a go-to step in my makeup routine. I mainly use it to brighten my undereye area. I'm impressed by how creamy yet lightweight the formula feels. It glides on smoothly without tugging at the skin, which is especially important for delicate areas around the eyes. On my skintone, the Light Bisque shade works perfectly to neutralize my dark circles without looking heavy or cakey.

What I love most is how natural the finish looks‚Äîit blends seamlessly with my concealer and doesn't crease, even after hours of wear. The stick format is also incredibly convenient for touch-ups on the go. I've worn it both during busy workdays and in the evenings, and it holds up well under different lighting, always giving my eyes a fresher and more awake appearance.

Overall, it's a reliable, everyday product that adds just the right amount of brightness. If you struggle with dark circles and want something easy to apply and comfortable to wear, this corrector stick is definitely worth trying.  I received this product for free from Bobbi Brown for testing and review purposes.
faceoff_positive.headline: Bye bye dark circles!

faceoff_negative.comments: I have used BB's corrector for many, many years.  I started with light bisque and then switched to extra light bisque when it was introduced.  Original light bisque was probably lighter before xtra light was developed. When the pot corrector was unavailable during the Black Friday and Christmas sales, I ordered two extra light bisque sticks. Assuming they were identical, I didn't use them until I finished my pot one.  Big mistake!  The colors of these sticks do not match the previous colors, this is almost white!  I now have two sticks I cannot use.  I bought one in light bisque to mix the two. Another waste.  This formula is drier than the previous one and creased horribly and accentuated all lines, even the tiniest!  So I have three corrector sticks that I cannot use and currently know of no good alternatives.  Cannot understand why they would change a beloved and original product from the line! They have also changed the pot concealer to this stick and reformulated the full coverage concealer to a drier more matte product who's colors also do not match the previous ones.  Idk why OG BB products are being reformulated except to make the parent company more money and stealing from the customers!  Do not buy anything unless you try in store first!  I used to stock up during sales, and now have 3 sticks I cannot use and have to spend time and money searching for alternatives. Very disappointed in what has happened to this line since Bobbi left the reins.
faceoff_negative.headline: Colors and texture not same as long beloved pot corrector
